The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Monday, January 31, 2005 

 ?Killer? guard held

 Midnapore, Jan. 30: S.K. Tewari, the Kolaghat Thermal Power Plant guard who killed 15-year-old Shampa Mondal when he shot at a group of suspected coal thieves yesterday, has been arrested.

 An employee of a private security agency, Tewari fired a round from his double-barrel gun when the group refused to move out of the complex, 70 km from Calcutta. The bullet hit Shampa, a student of Class IX in the local Khanjadapur High school, in the back. Her mother said she entered the plant to cut grass. 

 An official said the plant is guarded by 280 people ? National Volunteer Force personnel and home-guards. A group of 20 armed guards had been hired from a private agency. 

 East Midnapore police chief Maharathi Adhikary said a probe has been ordered. ?We will speak to all concerned ? villagers, security guards and plant officials.?




